# Preprocessed fake news text
import nltk
nltk.download('stopwords')
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
#removing stopwords, punctuations, numbers, urls, extra spaces
text = fake_news_df['text']
text = text.str.lower()
text = text.str.replace('[^\w\s]','')
text = text.str.replace('\d+', '')
text = text.str.replace('\s+', ' ')
text = text.str.replace('http\S+|www.\S+', '', case=False)
text = text.str.strip()

stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
text = [[word for word in doc.split() if word not in stop_words] for doc in text.tolist()]

text = [' '.join(doc) for doc in text]

text = text[0:100]

print(text[0])

In [32]:
from collections import Counter
# Creating bag of words
def make_bow(text, vocab):
    vocab_set = set(vocab)
    bow = []
    for doc in text:
        token_counts = Counter(doc.split())
        bow_doc = [int(token in vocab_set and token_counts[token] > 0) for token in vocab]
        bow.append(bow_doc)
    return bow
bow = make_bow(text, vocab)

Now lets come to the Clustering of our dataset. Here we use K means clustering and DB scan.

In [46]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

wcss = [] ### for storing wcss number

X_fake = fake_news_df[['followers', 'statuses_count']]


## your code goes here
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, init='k-means++', random_state=0, max_iter=300, n_init=10).fit(X_fake)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)

# Plotting the results onto a line graph to get the elbow
xaxis = [i for i in range(1, 11)]
plt.plot(xaxis, wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')

# Preprocessed real news text
import nltk

from nltk.corpus import stopwords

text = real_news_df['text']
text = text.str.lower()
text = text.str.replace('[^\w\s]','')
text = text.str.replace('\d+', '')

In [73]:
wcss = [] ### for storing wcss number

real_news_df = real_news_df.dropna()

X_real = real_news_df[['followers', 'statuses_count']]
X_real

## your code goes here
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, init='k-means++', random_state=0, max_iter=300, n_init=10).fit(X_real)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)


xaxis = [i for i in range(1, 11)]
plt.plot(xaxis, wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')

# initialize the DBSCAN algorithm
dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=5000, min_samples=100, metric='euclidean')

# fit the algorithm to the data
dbscan.fit(X_real)

# get the cluster labels
labels = dbscan.labels_
uniquelab = np.unique(labels)

# add the labels to the dataset
real_news_df['dbscan_label'] = labels

sns.scatterplot(x= X_real["followers"], y = X_real["statuses_count"], s = 25, hue=labels, palette = sns.color_palette("colorblind", len(uniquelab)))
plt.xlabel('Followers')
plt.ylabel('Statuses Count')
plt.title('DBSCAN Clustering Results')
plt.show()
